I’m a second year student studying computer science at the University of Virginia, interested in the intersection of data and people. I currently teach an introductory data science class at HackCville and have joined clubs that have allowed me to explore computer science in an interdisciplinary fashion. This diversity will allow me to be cognizant of biases when I develop algorithms and analyze data.

On a personal note, I’m the oldest of 4 siblings, I love to run, scuba dive, and volunteer with children in STEM!

If you are looking for interns, check out my resume. Or if you just want to reach out, please don’t hesitate to contact me!
